cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper focuses on using deep convolutional networks for image recognition tasks related to human rights violations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for recognition, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The topic of human rights violations may also suggest the paper could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of multimedia data (images) may suggest the paper could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
